<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Middle East Business Briefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, October 3 (Xinhua) -- The following are business briefs
of Middle East countries:
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- The first two foreign investment funds are set to be
injected in the Beirut Stock Exchange, Lebanon's newspaper the
Daily Star reported today.
</P>
<P>
The Regent Pacific group, an emerging market specialist based
in London and Hong Kong, has launched a 50 million U.S. dollars
fund to invest primarily in the Beirut bourse.
</P>
<P>
The fund, to be traded outside Lebanon, will also invest in
treasury bills and unlisted over-the-counter shares, the paper
said.
</P>
<P>
Societe Generale, the world's 29th biggest bank will launch a
similar fund next Monday to raise a maximum of 150 million
U.S. dollars to invest mainly in the stock markets of Lebanon,
Jordan, Egypt, Oman and Bahrain.
</P>
<P>
This will be the first time that wholly foreign firms have
earmarked funds for direct investments into Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
NICOSIA -- The Cyprus Stock Market maintained this week the
shallow, but continuous, sliding pattern exhibited last week,
according to a report issued by the Cyprus Investment and
Securities Corporation Limited (CISCO) today.
</P>
<P>
The report says trading volumes were rather suppressed with
interest remaining focused primarily on banking stocks and to a
lesser extent, insurance and industrial stocks.
</P>
<P>
The CISCO All-Share Index closed Thursday at 385.6 points,
having shed 4.3 points or 1.1 percent on the week.
</P>
<P>
The total weekly volume of transactions reached 2.3 million
Cyprus pounds (about 4.6 million U.S. dollars) this week,
compared to 4.1 million pounds (about 8.2 million dollars) the
week before.
</P>
<P>
NICOSIA -- Cyprus' trade deficit fell almost 4 percent in the
first five months of this year versus the same period in 1996,
according to a report issued today by the Department of
Statistics and Research.
</P>
<P>
Total exports decreased by 5.9 percent to 253 million
Cyprus pounds (about 506 million U.S. dollars), in the first
five months of 1997, compared with 269 million pounds (about
538 million dollars) in January-May 1996.
</P>
<P>
Total imports (covering items for home consumption and those
placed in bonded storage) fell 4.4 percent, to 765.7 million
pounds (about 1531.4 million dollars) this January-May, versus
801.3 million pounds (about 1602.6 million dollars) over the
same year-on-year period.
</P>
<P>
The result was a 3.7 percent trade deficit drop to 512.7
million pounds (about 1025.4 million dollars) this January-May,
compared to 532.4 million pounds (about 1064.8 million dollars)
year-on-year in 1996.
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- Strikers Holding, the parent company of Lebanon's
fifth largest insurance firm Strikers Insurance and Reinsurance,
has sold 51 percent of its shares to Bahrain-based Mediterranean
and Gulf Insurance and Reinsurance (MEDGULF).
</P>
<P>
The deal is seen as the start of consolidation in Lebanon's
over-crowded insurance sector, local newspapers reported today.
</P>
<P>
Strikers, a relative new-comer to the Lebanese insurance
scene, was founded in 1990 and ranks fifth behind Bankers,
Mesir, Lebanon-Suisse and Societe Nationale d'Assurances(SNA).
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the company had 14.14 million U.S. dollars in
earned premium. Its total assets stood at 14.06 million U.S.
dollars and shareholders' equity was 1.99 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
There are currently around 100 companies licensed to provide
insurance cover in Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- A new border gate along the Turkish-Syrian border is
to be opened later this week for trade between the two countries,
local newspapers reported.
</P>
<P>
Traders will be allowed to buy or sell goods no more than four
times a week through the gate, called Akcakale, in the
southeastern province of Sanli Urfa.
</P>
<P>
The volume of trade by one trader must be no more than 200,000
U.S. dollars for one month, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The opening of this new border gate is aimed at sharing the
burden on the heavily used Habur border gate, local officials said.
</P>
</TEXT>
