<HEADLINE> Pakistan to Eliminate Child Labor by 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan is committed to
eliminate child labor by the year 2000, a government official
said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the launching ceremony of the National UNICEF cards
campaign held Thursday in Lahore, Minister of Commerce Ishaq Dar
said that the government was establishing a task force to
eliminate child labor in the country.
</P>
<P>
According to Dar, the task force will consist of high-level
government officials, including those from the Ministries of
Commerce, Labor and Social Welfare.
</P>
<P>
A high-powered advisory committee would also be formed to
implement policies and plans recommended by the task force, said
the minister.
</P>
<P>
Dar said that the situation of children in Pakistan was
certainly not satisfactory and there was much to be desired.
</P>
<P>
"The problems faced by our children posed a serious challenge
to the nation," he added.
</P>
<P>
The main obstacle was lack of funding in the social sector, he
said, adding that the business community should come forward and
play an important role.  
</P>
</TEXT>
