<HEADLINE> Oman Supports Palestine: FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Oman today reaffirmed its
support for the Palestinian Authority position for an Israeli
withdrawal from the Palestinian territories occupied since 1967.
</P>
<P>
Oman has actively participated in supporting peace process in
the Middle East and demands that the relevant resolutions and
agreements be implemented in full, said Minister of State for
Foreign Affairs Yousef Alawi Abdullah.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the on-going 52nd session of the United Nations
General Assembly, he said Oman's stance stems from the reason that
peace serves the interests of all the people in the region.
</P>
<P>
Oman calls on the international community to enhance the preace
process by rendering support "both financially and logistically"
to the Palestinian Authority.
</P>
<P>
The support enables the Palestinian Authority to establish the
foundations for peace in territories and to build the economic
necessary infrastructures, he said.
</P>
<P>
The minister said Oman also supports the Syrian position for
the resumption of talks with Israel "based on the full and
complete Israeli withdrawal from the occupied Golan Hights".
</P>
<P>
"We would also like to reaffirm the importance of an Israeli
withdrawal form the occupied Lebanese terrorists to the
internationally recognized borders," he said.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized Oman's "absolute rejection of all forms of
violence and terrorism". 
</P>
</TEXT>
