<HEADLINE> Pak to Set up New Oil Refinery Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Pak Arab Refinery Limited
(PARCO) is to establish a new oil refinery near Multan in southern
Punjab province at a cost of 886 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Construction contract of the oil refinery named Mid Country
Refinery Project (MCRP) was awarded today to two Japanese
companies -- Marubeni Corporation and Japan Gasoline Corporation
(JGC).
</P>
<P>
MCRP is the first refinery after the lapse of 30 years of the
setting up of National Refinery Limited and Pakistan Refinery
Limited.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the Board of Directors of PARCO gave its final
approval for the award.
</P>
<P>
The oil refinery will have a daily capacity of 100,000 barrels
which is almost equivalent to the combined output of the existing
petroleum refining facilities in Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The project will reduce Pakistan's dependence on imported oil
products, saving 100 million dollars every year.
</P>
<P>
The oil refinery is expected to be completed by September 30,
2000 at a total cost of 886 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
There is an acute shortage of refining capacity in Pakistan,
which has dropped to only about 40 percent of its requirement.
Thus a major new refinery is a critical requirement for the
country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
