<HEADLINE> Pak Minister Calls for Greater Cooperation Among ECO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Minister of State
for Foreign Affairs Siddique Khan Kanju today called for greater
interaction among the countries of the Economic Cooperation
Organization (ECO) to make economic progress and face other social
and economic problems.
</P>
<P>
Talking to delegates of the ongoing conference of the ECO News
Agencies (ECONA) here, Kanju said that through the exchange of
news and enhancing professional skills, the ECO countries should
help to improve their image worldwide and solve their common
problems.
</P>
<P>
Welcoming the establishment of ECO News Agencies, he said it is
a welcome step in the right direction to educate the peoples of
their respective countries for economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The minister also briefed the delegates about the peace
initiatives taken by the Pakistani government on resolving the
Kashmir issue through dialogue.
</P>
<P>
Talking about the Afghan problem, the minister said the
conflict in Afghanistan is posing a threat to peace and it is the
responsibility of the ECO member states to bring warring factions
to the negotiation table for a broad-based government.
</P>
<P>
He said Pakistan is prepared to extend all possible cooperation
to resolve the problems confronted by the ECO member countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
