<HEADLINE> More Canadian Firms Listed on Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Canadian firms are going public
in growing numbers in 1997 and have found rich, fertile ground in
the capital markets, a report said today.
</P>
<P>
As of September 24, initial public offerings (IPOs) of Canadian
companies totaled 255, up 61 percent for the same period a year
earlier, only two deals short of the full-year record for 1996.
</P>
<P>
Even more dramatic is the rise in the total value of funds
raised through IPOs, according to the Financial Post newspaper.
</P>
<P>
IPO financings reached 8.8 billion dollars (6.3 billion USD),
up 175 percent over the amount raised in the same period last
year, and well ahead of 1996's total of 5.5 billion dollars (3.9
billion USD).
</P>
<P>
For the rest of the year, IPOs should at least maintain the
current pace, or even accelerate, the paper predicted.
</P>
<P>
The hottest component of the flood of new issues is income and
royalty trusts.
</P>
<P>
At 4.7 billion dollars (3.3 billion USD), the two accounted for
more than half of the value of all IPOs. 
</P>
