<HEADLINE> Hundreds Russian Generals to Be Unnecessary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 3 (Xinhua) -- A total of 425 Russian generals
will become redundant because of the military reform, reducing the
number of generals to 1,500, the Interfax quoted a Russian Defense
Ministry official as saying today.
</P>
<P>
The reduction will chiefly affect the Defense Ministry's
central structure, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Six instead of 12 army generals will remain in the armed
forces. The number of colonel-generals will be reduced from 169 to
67; of lieutenant-generals, from 470 to 353; and of major-generals
from 1,242 to 1,072.
</P>
<P>
Two positions of marshal of the Russian Federation will remain
in the ministry's structure. At the beginning of the year, the
possibility of having 32 of them was considered.
</P>
<P>
Ninety-two positions carrying the rank of general have already
been cut in the Defense Ministry's central structure, the official
said. 
</P>
