<DOCNO> XIE19971004.0031 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> African Countries Urged to Improve Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, October 3 (Xinhua) -- The International Association for
Educational Assessment (IAEA) today called on African countries
to form linkages with more advanced countries to find out a
workable solution to the problems of quality assessment in
education.
</P>
<P>
The issue of quality assessment is critical and imperative in
the education development as it affects the quality of life of
the individual and society and it is the gateway to future lives
of the students, said Frances Ottobre, an IAEA senior official.
</P>
<P>
According to the IAEA executive secretary, education
assessment in Africa is encouraging but needs a boost, thus she
urged the governments to provide the funds and facilities for
improved quality assessment.
</P>
<P>
"African countries should make educational assessment a
priority in their national policies in order to produce quality
citizens and improve on survival strategies and skills," she
said, quoted by the News Agency of Nigeria.  
</P>
</TEXT>
