<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mortgage Rates Drop in Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Canada's major commercial banks
announced today a drop of 10 to 25 basis points in long-term
mortgage rates.
</P>
<P>
Under the new rate effective tomorrow, the two-year mortgage
rates falls by 10 basis points to 6.05 percent, and the 25-year
rate by 25 basis points to 8.25 percent.
</P>
<P>
However, mortgage rates of six months to one year did not
change at all.
</P>
<P>
The latest round of mortgage rate cut came on the heels of a
positive U.S. employment report today, which sent interest rates
in North America bond markets much lower.
</P>
<P>
Commercial banks finance most of their long-term mortgages on
the bond market.
</P>
<P>
Cheaper borrowing costs usually lead to a drop in the long-term
mortgage rates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
