<HEADLINE> Access to Sex Education Vital to Youth: Professor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, October 3 (Xinhua) -- A public health professor
appeals that adolescents have the right of access to sex
information and services so that they could manage their sexual
and reproductive life in a responsive and informed way.
</P>
<P>
Fear about family life education (FLE) and access to
contraception would encourage productivity at an early stage,
Professor E. Mhondwa warned at a workshop being held in Morogoro,
Tanzania News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Denial of this right would make most young people ill-informed
about their sexual and reproductive life, Mhondwa said.
</P>
<P>
The professor was presenting a paper on "Adolescent, Sexual
and Reproductive Health" at a five-day workshop on safe
motherhood initiatives and adolescent health.
</P>
<P>
The workshop, organized by the Health Education Unit of the
Ministry of Health, is expected to end on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
He said adolescents are facing a number of risks such as HIV
and AIDS infections, sexually transmitted diseases (STDS) and
unwanted pregnancies, if they are not well informed on sexual and
reproductive behaviors.
</P>
<P>
Profesdsor Muhondwa said health education message in the media
should address such issues as behaviors, beliefs and practices in
the youth community. 
</P>
