<HEADLINE> French FM to Visit South Africa, Ethiopia, Cote d'Ivoire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 3 (Xinhua) -- French Foreign Minister Hubert
Vedrine will visit South Africa, Ethiopia and Cote d'Ivoire next
week, announced French Foreign Ministry spokesman Jacques
Rummelhardt today.
</P>
<P>
This will be the first time for the French foreign minister to
visit sub-Saharan Africa since taking office in June.
</P>
<P>
"One should have an African policy of a continental scale,
instead of one limited to a group of countries," said the
spokesman in reference to the new African policy adopted lately by
France.
</P>
<P>
After the overthrow of the power of former President Mobutu
Sese Seko in ex-Zaire and the upheavals in Central African
Republic and Congo Republic earlier this year, France decided to
reduce its military force in Africa and develop relations with
English-speaking countries.
</P>
<P>
"We should act on all fronts, think about the new elites (of
African countries), have an open economic policy, have a global
vision of Africa, a modernization, an adaption which is a shared
project of the president and the government," said Rummelhardt.
</P>
<P>
Vedrine will visit Capetown, Addis Abeba, where is located the
headquarters of the Organization of African Unity, and Abidjan on
October 9-11. 
</P>
</TEXT>
