<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Food Output to Surpass 30 Million tons this year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's total food output is
estimated to reach 30.6 million tons of rice equivalent this
year, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The figure makes 1997 to be the 10th consecutive year that vietnam
achieves year-on-year increasing in food production.
</P>
<P>
Unprocessed rice is estimated to reach 27.7 million tons,
up by 1.3 million tons compared to last year, while unprocessed
rice-equivalent subsidiary crops amounting to 2.9 million tons.
</P>
<P>
Farmers throughout the country harvested 13.3 million tons of
unprocessed rice from nearly 2.67 million hectares in the last
winter-spring crop, an increase of 1.1 million tons over the same crop
of the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The cultivation acreage for this year's summer-autumn crop
shrank to 2.5 million hectares due to flood invasion in the Mekong
Delta. However, this crop is expected to yield 7.9 million tons
of food. 
</P>
</TEXT>
