<HEADLINE> Hezbollah Is Training Militants from </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or
Party of God, has said that it is training Muslim militants from
the Palestinian Hamas and Islamic Jihad movements in Lebanon,
local weekly Haramoun magazine reported today.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the magazine, Sheikh Naee'm Kassem,
Hezbollah deputy secretary-general, said the groups had
coordinated in the past.
</P>
<P>
"If training is needed we are able to do it and we are ready
to do it," he said.
</P>
<P>
"In some instances we have done that (the training)," he
added.
</P>
<P>
Asked if the training had taken place in Lebanon, he said, "In
Lebanon, and this is a natural matter."
</P>
<P>
"We are still doing this until now. And we are prepared to do
everything to help in the confrontation with Israel," he added.
</P>
<P>
The armed wing of Hamas which opposed to Israel's peace deal
with the Palestine Liberation Organizaton (PLO) has killed scores
of people in suicide bombings in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Islamic Jihad, a Palestinian group smaller than Hamas that
also opposed to current Middle East peace process, has carried
out other suicide bombings in Israel.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah, Israel's most active and dreaded enemy in Lebanon,
threatened in August during a funeral procession for Hezbollah
guerrillas to carry out suicide bombings inside Israel. 
</P>
