<HEADLINE> Private Business Grows in Jiangsu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Private business in east China's
Jiangsu province has been growing steadly with a turnout of 31
billion yuan (3.8 billion US dollars) last year.
</P>
<P>
The figure accounted for 11 percent of the total industrial
added value of the province, local officials said.
</P>
<P>
By the end of August, the province had boasted 1.2 million
private enterprises, shops and other businesses with a total of
2.72 million employees.
</P>
<P>
Since 1987, the private sector has paid 19.76 billion yuan
(2.38 billion US dollars) in taxes to the state coffer.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu's private businesses employeed some 120,000 laid-off
workers last year. In the first half of this year, the figure
reached 103,000, official figures show.  
</P>
