<HEADLINE> Nepal Has Rich Species of Reptiles and Amphibians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Nepal has some 100 species of
reptiles and 43 species of amphibians, the RSS news agency
reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Of the 100 reptilian species, three species, namely gavial
crocodile (gharial), iguana and python, are protected under the
country's Wild Life Protection Act as they are under great threat
due to the loss of habitat as a result of human incursion, the RSS
said.
</P>
<P>
An organization called Amphibians and Reptiles Conservation in
Nepal Society has been set up in Germany with the objective of
assisting the conservation and development programs for these
species, the RSS quoted the Nepali Forest and Soil Conservation
Ministry as saying.  
</P>
</TEXT>
