<HEADLINE> Zhejiang Cultural Relics to Be Shown in Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Some 229 cultural relics, found
in southeast China's Zhejiang Province and dating back to more than
7,000 years, will soon be on show in Japan.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of the exhibit is to celebrate the 25th anniversary
of the normalization of Sino-Japanese relations and the fifth
anniversary of the establishment of friendly relations between
Zhejiang Province of China and Fukui Prefecture of Japan.
</P>
<P>
The Zhejiang Museum spent two years selecting relics for the show,
to be held in Fukui.
</P>
<P>
The exhibits include coins in ancient China and Hangzhou silk
produced in the Qing Dynasty (1644-1911). Of them, 11 pieces are
listed as first-class State relics. 
</P>
