<HEADLINE> World Animal Day Marked in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 4 (Xinhua) -- The World Animal Day was marked
today in the southern outskirtan area of the capital city of
Beijing with a special party arranged for pet dogs and cats.
</P>
<P>
Some 300 naturalists and animal protectionists gathered at a
center for the protection of endangered animals in the Donghu Wood
in Daxing county, some 40 km from the downtown area. A concert was
held for animals living there, and a big cake was presented.
</P>
<P>
A short-distance run was arranged for the human's best friend
-- the dogs. A grey dog named "Dodo" won the championship and was
awarded with a bowl of pet's food.
</P>
<P>
Experts were busy than ever providing consultant services for
animal fans. "Thousands of animal species have bidden farewell to
the mankind in the outgoing 20th century. And we people on earth
should take lenient attitude toward wildlife and keep the balance
between different species," said Qi Hanjun, a researcher with the
center.
</P>
<P>
October 4 was designated from the 1920s as the World Animal Day
in commemoration of an Italian animal protectionist of the 19th
century, who proposed establishing a brotherhood between the man
and animals. 
</P>
