<HEADLINE> Kuwaiti Stock Index Up in Third Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, October 4 (Xinhua) -- The Kuwait Stock Exchange
(KSE) market index hiked 200.5 points in the third quarter to
close at 2602.4 points on September 30, according to the bourse
report of the quarter today.
</P>
<P>
The report said total shares in trading amounted to 6.6 billion
U.S. dollars in the period.
</P>
<P>
It said share values of 42 companies out of a total of 72 in
trading increased while shares of 24 companies dropped.
</P>
<P>
Average daily trading was 96.2 million shares for 30.5 million
dinars (100 million U.S. dollars) and over 2000 deals.
</P>
<P>
It said the investment sector topped the trading, followed by
the industrial sector and the real estate sector.
</P>
<P>
The bourse's Director General Hisham Al-Oteibi said last week
that the KSE market capitalization was at 26 billion dollars for
the listed companies.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait bourse has been operating well since last year and only
nationals of Gulf Arab states including Saudi Arabia, Bahrain, the
United Arab Emirates, Qatar, Oman and Kuwait can trade on the
exchange.
</P>
<P>
It has entered into agreements with several other Arab
countries including Egypt, Lebanon and Bahrain to allow their
investors to cross-trade on each other's markets.
</P>
<P>
Other non-Gulf Arab foreigners could be allowed to trade on
the KSE in the coming few months, according to a KSE plan to open
the exchange market to more foreign investors.
</P>
<P>
Presently, Kuwait's 1.25 million foreign residents can invest
through three listed mutual funds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
