<HEADLINE> Paint Industry Booming in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 4 (Xinhua) -- China's paint-manufacturing
industry has experienced a booming era in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the Chinese Paint Industry Association showed
that the total paint output of China reached 1.5 million tons last
year, ranking fifth in the world.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has made great efforts to develop
the industry since the late 1970s. To date, the country has set
up a number of bases producing a variety of paint
products such as construction paint, automobile paint, and
anti-corrosive paint.
</P>
<P>
Chinese experts predict that by the year 2000, the country will
need 700,000 tons of industrial paint, 905,000 tons of
construction paint, and 300,000 tons of anti-corrosive paint.
