<HEADLINE> South Korea Take Straight Wins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, October 4 (Xinhua) -- South Korea downed the United Arab
Emirates 3-0 here Saturday in the Asian World Cup Group B
quarlifier, keeping unbeaten with a maximum 12 points from four
wins.
</P>
<P>
Kazakhstan held Japan to a 1-1 draw at home after a 0-1
halftime trail.
</P>
<P>
Though the defeat, the United Arab Emirates remain in second
place in the group B with 2-1-1 in a win-draw-loss record. Japan
was third with 1-2-1. Kazakhstan(two draws and two losses) and
Uzbekistan (one draw and three losses) are the last two.
</P>
<P>
Ha Seok-Ju put South Korea on the lead eight minutes into the
match when he beat two defenders to send the ball into the net.
</P>
<P>
Inspired by the 60,000 crowd packing the Chamsil Olympic
Stadium, Koreans scored the other two in the second half with one
penalty in the 67th minute by Yoo Sang-Chul and a one way goal
with 10 minutes left by Lee Sang-Yoon.
</P>
<P>
The United Arab Emirates almost equalized in the 21st minute
when Ali Hassan Gholam's 20-meter shot stormed against the post.
</P>
<P>
Japan's hopes to the World Cup finals was hung by a thread
after Viktor Zubarev made even in injury time to tie the home
match.
</P>
<P>
Japan led most of the match after Yutaka Akita headed in the
22nd minute from Hiroshi Nanami's pass. 
