<HEADLINE> Ramos Hails Passage of Anti-Poverty Bill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
today hailed the passage of the anti-poverty bill by the House of
Representatives on Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
Ramos said the passage of the bill was a major step towards the
implementation of the government's poverty alleviation program
which was called the Social Reform Agenda.
</P>
<P>
The bill seeks to directly finance and support pro-poor
projects, particularly those in the country's 20 poorest provinces
and 1,000 municipalities, he said.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that some 35 percent of the country's
population were poor people. To fight poverty, the Ramos
administration has set up a special council and allocated a total
of 1.6 billion pesos (61 million U.S. dollars) in the past few
years.
</P>
<P>
The anti-poverty bill must be also approved by the Senate
before being signed into law by the President. 
