<HEADLINE> Military Officials from Six Countries to Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Senior military officials from
six countries, who are currently studying in London, will visit
Uganda on October 7-12, Radio Uganda reported today.
</P>
<P>
The group will include senior officers from the British army,
Royal Navy and Royal Air Force, as well as from the armed forces
of Canada, Germany, Austria, Indonesia and Oman.
</P>
<P>
The visit is part of the group's one-year course of studies at
the British Royal College of Defense in London.
</P>
<P>
Each year about 80 military and government officials attend
the prestigious course, with approximately half from countries
other that Britain.
</P>
<P>
The participants are being prepared for high responsibility in
the management of defense, security and related areas.
</P>
<P>
The group's African tour is aimed for the officials to learn
as much as possible about African countries' defense concerns and
political, social and economic policies.
</P>
<P>
While in Uganda, the group is scheduled to meet Ugandan
President Y. Museveni, Minister of State for Defense Amama
Mbabazi, Army Commander Major General Mugisha Muntu and other
senior army officers and to visit the parliament. 
</P>
