<HEADLINE> Mozambican Premier Hails China for Taking Back </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican Premier Pascoal
Mocumbi today congratulated the Chinese people on China's
resumption of its sovereignty over Hong Kong in July.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua before an unofficial visit to
China, the first since he became premier in 1994, Mocumbi said
China's resumption of its sovereignty over Hong Kong was a great
success with historic significance to the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
It shows that the political aspirations of the Chinese people
could not be renounced at any time, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The premier said, "I very much appreciated China's method of
taking back Hong Kong, and I congratulated the Chinese people on
their success."
</P>
<P>
He said his forthcoming visit to China is aimed at
strengthening the friendship and cooperation between the two
peoples. And as foreign minister, Mocumbi had paid a visit to
China in 1992.
</P>
<P>
"I'd like to see with my own eyes the profound changes China
has been undergoing in recent years so that we can learn from it
and apply its experience to the ongoing reforms in Mozambique,"
said the premier.
</P>
<P>
Mocumbi said China and Mozambique can cooperate in the fields
of farming, processing agro-products and industry, and that China
can invest in these aspects or run joint ventures in Mozambique
so as to provide products in local markets or export them to its
neighbors.
</P>
<P>
When meeting with local reporters Friday, the Mozambican
premier said he hoped to meet Chinese Premier Li Peng during his
China visit. 
</P>
