<HEADLINE> Kororia Wins World Half-Marathon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Kenyans showed again their
domination of the long distance running Saturday by sweeping three
of the four golds on offer in the world half-marathon
Championships in Kosice, Slovakia.
</P>
<P>
Kenyans claimed a 1-2-3 finish in the men's individual
competition, with Shem Kororia leading the sprint over the final
kilometer to clinch the title in 59 minutes and 56 seconds, the
second fastest for the 21 kilometers distance and a Championships
best.
</P>
<P>
Kororia was followed by compatriot Moses Tanui in second and
Kenneth Cheruiyot third, timing 59:58 and one hour respectively.
</P>
<P>
Kenya also took the men's team gold medal.
</P>
<P>
Tecla Loroupe of Kenya won the women's individual champion in
one hour eight minutes 14 seconds. She ran away from her rivals
just after the halfway mark.
</P>
<P>
Cristina Pomacu was second in 1:08.43 with fellow Romanian
Lidia Simon third in 1:09.05.
</P>
<P>
The two Romanians added women's team gold medals after beating
Kenya in a close contest. 
</P>
</TEXT>
