<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Kazakh President Nursultan
Nazarbayev held talks today with visiting Russian Prime Minister
Viktor Chernomyrdin. Both sides agreed that problems would not
become hurdles to developing good bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin arrived here today for a two-day working
visit; trade between the two former Soviet republics plunged
by 30 percent in the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
The Russian prime minister said the plunge should be attributed
to the taxation policies of the two countries, which, he said, could
be solved through mutual efforts.
</P>
<P>
He noted that despite divergences and problems, relations
between his country and Kazakhstan are solid.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders also discussed Russia's rent for the Baikonur
Cosmodrome in Kazakhstan.
</P>
<P>
The two countries signed agreements after the meeting on
strengthening environmental protection in the Baikonur region and
on the rational use of natural resources.
</P>
<P>
Describing Russia as a country with important political and
economic influences in the international community, Nazarbayev
stressed relations with Russia will take a priority in
Kazakhstan's diplomacy.
</P>
<P>
He said a joint committee will be established to negotiate
problems in bilateral relations. 
