<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Advertising Industry Records Rapid Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 4 (Xinhua) -- China's advertising industry has
enjoyed a rapid and sustained development in the past five years.
</P>
<P>
The trade was among the country's fastest growing sector with
the number of advertising firms tripling and their business
turnover increasing by nearly tenfold in the five-year period from
1992 to 1997.
</P>
<P>
So far, 300 firms are Sino-foreign joint ventures or operating
in the form of cooperation. Among them, the two prestigious
advertising groups, namely, the China Union Advertising Corp. and
China Foreign Trade Advertising Group, took on some one third of
the business of the trade.
</P>
<P>
The business turnover of Shanghai and Beijing municipalities
and south China's Guangdong Province made up 46 percent of the
national total, estimating at 16.7 billion yuan (two billion US
dollars) in the 1992-97 period.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the amount of profits gained by advertising on
television came to 90.8 billion yuan (10.9 billion US dollars) and
that on newspapers amounted to 7.77 billion yuan (936 million US
dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
