of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) of China,
has appointed Anna Wu as chairman of the Consumer Council for two
years as from October 1997, a government spokesman announced here
today.
</P>
<P>
John Ho Dit-sang has been appointed by Financial Secretary
Donald Tsang Yam-kuen as the council's vice-chairman for the same
period, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Wu joined the Consumer Council in 1989 and became its
vice-chairman in 1993. She is very active in the council's affairs
 and leads, among others, the Legal Protection Committee and the
Consumer Legal Action Fund Management Committee. She also serves
as vice-chairman of the Competition Policy Committee.
</P>
<P>
Ho, who joined the council in 1993, has been involved in
various committees and working groups and is now vice-chairman of
the council's Trade Practices Committee.
</P>
<P>
"We are confident that Ms. Wu and Dr. Ho will provide the
necessary leadership for the council in continuing to promote
consumer interests in Hong Kong," the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Wu will be succeeding Edward Chen Kwan-yiu, who will be
retiring form the Consumer Council after having served on it for
10 years, including six years as chairman.  
