<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pudong Raises Funds from Diversified Sources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 4 (Xinhua) -- The Pudong New Area, a new
powerhouse of Shanghai's economy, has raised funds from
diversified channels.
</P>
<P>
Pudong has drawn a total fixed asset investment of 120 billion
yuan over the past seven years, with some 10 percent coming from
the central, municipal and local governments, according to a
recent survey by the Pudong New Area Administrative Commission.
</P>
<P>
Foreign funds accounted 32 percent of total investments, with
bank loans and funds raised by enterprises making up 28 percent
and 30 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Pudong has been a focal point of foreign investment since its
establishment seven years ago and, and attracted contractual
foreign funds of 5.8 billion US dollars for real estate and
infrastructure development by the end of 1996, according to
research carried out by Fudan University.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investors have expressed confidence in Pudong's future
prospects as a leading economic, financial and trade center, and
its position as one of the world's most favorable investment
environments.
</P>
<P>
Pudong has introduced the BOT (build, operate and transfer)
method to encourage foreign investment in infrastructure
development. The method enables foreign investors to invest,
manage and operate the projects prior to transfering same to the
local government when contracts expire. 
</P>
</TEXT>
