<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan Ratifies International Convention on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan has ratified the
International Convention on Nuclear Safety which came into force
on October 22 last year.
</P>
<P>
According to a press statement here today, Pakistan signed the
convention on September 20, 1994.
</P>
<P>
The convention seeks to strengthen international technical
co-operation in enhancing the safe operation of land-based civil
nuclear power plants, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
It also envisages provision to all the member states of access
to the latest technology and expertise in the field of nuclear
safety through the International Atomic Energy Agency.
</P>
<P>
Having become a party to the convention, Pakistan will be
working in close cooperation with other member states for the
purpose of promoting an effective nuclear safety culture as
envisaged under the convention, the statement said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
