<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Delegation Ends Visit to Estonia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TALLINN, Estonia, October 3 (Xinhua) -- A delegation of China's
National People's Congress (NPC), the country's top legislature,
today ended a five-day visit to Estonia.
</P>
<P>
Winding up the tour, NPC Standing Committee Vice-chairman Tomur
Dawamat said the Chinese group had achieved all of its goals
through exchanges with leaders of the Estonian Riigikogu, or
parliament.
</P>
<P>
The better understanding between the two legislatures would
further the friendship between the two peoples, the head of the
Chinese delegation told the Estonia, a national newspaper here.
</P>
<P>
Tomur also expressed thanks, through the news outlet, for the
hospitality offered by his Estonian hosts.
</P>
<P>
During his stay, Tomur met Estonian President Lennart Meri at a
reception hosted by the Chinese embassy to mark the 48th
anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
He also discussed with President Toomas Savi and Vice President
Tunne Kelam of the Estonian parliament about continued efforts to
promote the NPC's interchanges with its Estonian counterpart.
</P>
<P>
On the Sino-Estonian trade ties, he noted in his interview with
the Estonia that there are still great potentials yet to be tapped
after the notable growth of bilateral trade volume in recent years.
</P>
<P>
The delegation left for Minsk this afternoon for a five-day
visit to Belarus. 
</P>
</TEXT>
