<DOCNO> XIE19971004.0119 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan Urges Tension Reduction Between West, Islam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani President Farooq
Leghari today stressed the need to promote a better understanding
between the West and the Islamic world by reducing tensions,
surfacing owing to "presumptions and deep-seated biases."
</P>
<P>
"Once we succeed in developing a proper perspective for mutual
understanding we shall ipso facto enhance our ability to come out
of our cocoons of isolation," Leghari told a seminar here on
"Western Perceptions of Muslims; Muslims Perceptions of West."
</P>
<P>
The three-day seminar has been organized jointly by Islamic
Research Institute and International Islamic University.
</P>
<P>
The president said it is ironical that despite latest
communication in the post-Cold War era, the ability of the West
and the Islamic world to understand each other is "strikingly
limited and deficient."
</P>
<P>
Leghari said cross-cultural interaction has always been
beneficial as no civilization or society could progress in
isolation. Rather the people of one culture can understand
themselves by knowing the cultures of others, he added.
</P>
<P>
He said history would verify that all the civilizations that
seek to thrive on cultivating the myths of superiority or absolute
monopoly of knowledge and wisdom are doomed to perdition sooner or
later.
</P>
<P>
Leghari said there are people who talk of the impending clash
of civilization but there is also a silver lining on the horizon.
</P>
<P>
It is encouraging to observe cordiality and empathy emerging
out of the various initiatives for inter-religious and
inter-civilizational dialogues organized in recent years, he
noted.
</P>
<P>
Leghari believed that a great deal of suffering faced by
humanity could have been averted if sincere effort had been made
to understand the others and appreciate the positive elements in
their cultures, religions and heritage.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
