<DOCNO> XIE19971004.0124 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 89 Killed in Latest Algeria Massacre </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 4 (Xinhua) -- At least 89 people were massacred,
some of them mutilated and decapitated, in a series of killings
committed since Thursday in the regions of Algiers, Medea and Oran
in Algeria, according to reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
The city of Blida, 40 kilometers south of Algiers, was attacked
with a number of home-made rockets Friday night, in which at least
four were killed and many others injured, reported Agence
France-Presse quoting witnesses.
</P>
<P>
In the village of Mellaha, which is situated on the plain of
Mitidja south of Algiers, 38 people -- including women and
children -- had their throats cut or were slaughtered with axes
from Thursday night to Friday morning.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-seven people, including 15 agricultural workers, were
killed in Medea, 80 kilometers south of Algiers, early Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Fourteen others were killed near Oran, which is the second
largest city in Algeria west of Algiers, on Thursday by an armed
group.
</P>
<P>
This is the first collective killing of this fashion in Oran
which has ever been reported.
</P>
<P>
The newest killings took place after Algerian President Liamine
Zeroual rejected a call for talks by the outlawed Islamic
Salvation Front (FIS).
</P>
<P>
The Islamic Salvation Army, which is the military wing of FIS,
started a unilateral ceasefire with government forces from October
1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
