<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Military Co-operation Between China and Kazakhstan Stressed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 4 (Xinhua) -- General Chi Haotian,
vice-chairman of China's Central Military Commission, held talks
with Muhtar Alteinbaev, defense minister of Kazakhstan, here today.
</P>
<P>
Chi said that China and Kazakhstan are neighbors closely linked
by waters and mountains, and have maintained a long-term and
profound friendship.
</P>
<P>
Since the two countries established diplomatic relations, their
co-operation in various sectors has witnessed smooth progress
through joint efforts, Chi said, adding co-operation between the
two armed forces has been expanding along with the growth of
bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
At present, military co-operation is developing in different
sectors at different levels, said Chi, who is also state
councillor and defense minister. He expressed the conviction that
Alteinbaev's current visit will surely unveil a new chapter of
military co-operation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
China, as a developing socialist country, will build its army
along a course with Chinese characteristic and will never seek
hegemonism, nor join any military alliance, nor deploy a single
soldier abroad, he emphasized.
</P>
<P>
He cited President Jiang Zemin's announcement at the recently
concluded 15th National Congress of the Chinese Communist Party
that China will cut another 500,000 armed personnels in addition
to the one million military personnel cut in the 1980s, saying the
decision serves as a good proof.
</P>
<P>
China firmly sticks to the independent foreign policy of peace,
and is willing to establish a good-neighborly relations oriented
to the 21st century together with Kazakhstan, in a bid to jointly
safeguarding the world peace, stability and development, he said.
</P>
<P>
Alteinbaev said that Kazakhstan is paying attention to learning
from other countries in its own national defense construction, and
the Chinese People's Liberation Army, with a history of 70 years,
has rich experience worth drawing on.
</P>
<P>
Kazakhstan and China share a boundary line of 1,700 km, and the
co-operation between their border areas is an important reflection
of their good-neighborliness, Alteinbaev said, adding it is of
great significance for the two armed forces to strengthen their
contacts.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the belief that the friendly co-operation between
the two countries as well as the two armed forces will be advanced.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the talks, Chi presided over a welcoming ceremony in
honor of Alteinbaev. Alteinbaev and his party arrived in Beijing
yesterday to begin their China trip as guests of General Chi.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
