<HEADLINE> 125 Gold Biscuits Seized in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Indian customs officials have
seized here 125 gold biscuits valued at 6.7 million rupees (about
190,000 U.S. dollars) in the local market, the local press said
today.
</P>
<P>
The gold biscuits were reportedly seized on Thursday night from
a 60-year-old passenger, Subhash Gandhi, who had concealed the
biscuits in a pair of shoes.
</P>
<P>
The passenger's brother was also found to be carrying 300 grams
of gold and other dutiable goods valued at 400,000 rupees (about
11,400 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Acting on special information, customs officials had been
keeping watch on Air India Flight 726, which had arrived from
Dubai, the United Arab Emirates.
</P>
<P>
After the flight landed at the international airport here, the
officials followed the two brothers till the Immigration area.
</P>
<P>
After they came out of the green channel, the brothers were
diverted for a thorough check which resulted in the seizure of the
gold biscuits.  
