for next year's World Cup finals in France.
</P>
<P>
The American team remained third in the North and Central
American qualifying group with 10 points from two wins, four draws
and one loss.
</P>
<P>
Jamaica moved to top of the group with 12 points and two games
to play. They are now favored to qualify to the World Cup finals
for the first time in history.
</P>
<P>
The top three teams of the group qualify for the 1998 World Cup
finals. 
