States agreed to conduct more efficient cooperation in regional
security after a one-day meeting here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The successful meeting will have an active impact on security
in the region as well as in Europe as a whole, defense ministers
from Albania, Bulgaria, Romania, Slovenia, Macedonia, Italy,
Greece, Turkey and the U.S. told reporters at a joint press
conference after the meeting.
</P>
