<HEADLINE> Fresh quake Hits Central Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Another powerful earthquake struck
central Italy again today after two strong tremors a week ago, the
ANSA news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The latest tremor on Friday occurred at 10:55 a.m. local time
(0855 gmt) with a magnitude of 5.1 on the Richter scale. It was
centered on the mountain town of Colfiorito in Umbria, 10
kilometers from the epicenter of last week's quakes. At least 20
people suffered slight injuries.
</P>
<P>
Last week's quakes, measuring 5.5 and 5.6, killed 11 people.
</P>
<P>
A series of aftershocks followed, including a tremor with a
magnitude of 3.5 at 1:04 p.m. (1104 gmt) and another almost as
strong about 40 minutes later.
</P>
<P>
Friday's quake caused more damage to the frescoed interior of
the 13th century Basilica of St. Francis in Assisi, said an
official of the basilica's museum.
</P>
<P>
Part of the cathedral's vaulted ceiling collapsed during last
week's quakes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
