<HEADLINE> China Sets to Drill New Offshore Oil Field </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, October 4 (Xinhua) -- China plans to drill oil from
the central region of the Bohai Sea, some 100 kilometers away from
the northern port city of Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
The offshore oil fields, Qinhuangdao 32-6 and Nanbao 35-2, were
found in 1995. Experimental drillings have been done to verify the
storage and prospects.
</P>
