<BODY>
<HEADLINE> WTO Calls for Advancement in Multilateralism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, October 3 (Xinhua) -- World Trade Organization (WTO)
General Director Renato Ruggiero today called on Latin American
and Asian-Pacific rim countries to advance more rapidly in the
implementation of a multilateral commerce system.
</P>
<P>
The WTO chief made this call in his speech at the meeting of
economy and commerce ministers of Latin America and the
Asia-Pacific rim countries being held here, where the Economic
Commission for Latin America and the Caribbean (Cepal) is based.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is aimed at getting both regions more closely
linked.
</P>
<P>
Ruggiero considered "erroneous" the opinion that globalization
will provoke a wider gap between the rich and the poor.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that the correct procedure to be successful in
the new international commerce scenario is to combine efficient
macroeconomic policies with the globalization process promoted by
the WTO.
</P>
<P>
In the meanwhile, he said, the present trend toward regionalism
must be considered complementary to global multilateralism.
</P>
<P>
He said if the world does not advance on this line, instead of
"globalizing regionalism, we are going to regionalize
globalization."
</P>
<P>
Ruggiero also highlighted interest shown by both regions to
publicize their economic data at the WTO Internet sites. 
</P>
</TEXT>
