<HEADLINE> Mercosur-ASEAN Businessmen Council to Be Create </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Businessmen in the Southern
Common Market (Mercosur) and the Association of Southeast Asian
Nations (ASEAN) agreed here today to create a joint business
council to increase the commercial links between the two blocs.
</P>
<P>
The project was received by Argentine government officials and
ASEAN General Secretary Dato Ajit Singh, who arrived in Argentina
with Malaysia Prime Minister Dato Seri Mahathir bin Mohamad for an
official visit.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN groups Brunei, Philippines, Indonesia, Laos,
Malaysia, Myanmar, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam and the
Mercosur comprises Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay.
</P>
<P>
Businessmen from the two regional groupings joined Argentine
exporters in a national gathering inaugurated by Argentine
President Carlos Menem.
</P>
<P>
The gathering followed the one they had earlier this week in
Santiago, Chile, during the 12th annual meeting of the Pacific
Economic Cooperation Council (PECC).
</P>
<P>
The PECC, which Argentina and Brazil have been invited to join,
groups 23 countries in Asia and America.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN is a bloc with a population of 480 million and a gross
domestic product of 711 U.S. billion dollars and the Mercosur has
a population of 200 million and a gross domestic product of 980
billion dollars. 
</P>
