<HEADLINE> Priceless Neolithic Treasure in Greece Turned Over </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, October 3 (Xinhua) -- A priceless collection of
neolithic gold artifacts seized by Greek police in a swoop
operation Monday was turned over to the state today in a ceremony
at the Greek Culture Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The collection of 54 gold rings, beads and pendants, dating
back to the 5th millennium B.C., will be permanently exhibited at
the National Archaeological Museum as of early December.
</P>
<P>
The treasures weigh a mere 232 grams in total, but their value
to researchers of the neolithic age was reported to be
immeasurable.
</P>
<P>
This was the largest quantity of gold jewelry of the neolithic
era ever found, said Dr. Ekaterini Dimakopoulos, director of the
National Archaeological Museum in Athens and an expert on the
prehistoric period. 
</P>
