<HEADLINE> Greek Annual Inflation Drops Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, October 3 (Xinhua) -- The annual consumer price
inflation in Greece dropped sharply from 5.6 percent in August to
4.9 percent in September.
</P>
<P>
The general consumer price index (CPI) increased 1.7 percent in
September, compared to an increase of 2.3 percent in the same
month of 1996, the Greek National Statistics Service (NSS)
announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The CPI increase in September was shaped as a result of a 0.5
percent drop in foodstuff, a 9.6 percent increase in clothing and
footwear and a 4.3 percent increase in durable consumer goods.
</P>
<P>
The NSS said that the downward trend of inflation would
continue. 
