The details for withdrawing 1,100 French troops from the
country's capital Bangui was still being worked out.
</P>
<P>
France has two military bases in the Central Africa Republic.
The bases were set up in accordance with the defense agreement
signed in 1960s between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Earlier last July, France announced that it would be reducing
the number of French troops stationed on the African continent
from 8000 to 5000.
</P>
<P>
The cut includes the closure of Bouar base which has served
for many French military operations in central Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
