<HEADLINE> London, Paris Shares Set New Record Highs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Europe's two major stock markets
London and Paris staged strong gains today and ended the week with
fresh closing highs, boosted by Wall Street's early rally and
benign US economic figures.
</P>
<P>
Share prices on the London market rose sharply to hit a new
closing high of 5,330.8, up 34.7 points on the day and 104.5
points higher over the week as the Dow rallied on the back of
subdued US jobs figures.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE 100 index was already boosted by a subdued purchasing
managers' survey of UK services earlier in the day, dealers said.
</P>
<P>
Leading French shares also made big gains today, with the
CAC-40 index surging to a new closing high of 3,094.01, 41.94
points higher, breaching the earlier closing record of 3,075.67
set on July 31 and a rise of 108.38 points on the week.
</P>
<P>
The market was boosted by good corporate results and fresh
strength on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
The Frankfurt market was closed today for a public holiday. The
DAX-30 index ended 76.73 points higher at 4,273.71 Thursday.
Trading will resume Monday. 
</P>
